Substance use factors: plotting rg with other traits

We compare the correlation between the identified factors and a selection of other traits. To harmonize the color scheme across the different models, we use grey for F1/ G, blue for smoking, purple for alcohol, green for cannabis, red for dependence,

By EFA factor

We start with the correlations between the external traits and the factors from the EFA-based standard 4-factor model. Filled point estimates indicate that the rg is significant after FDR correction within category. Asterisks indicate per factor (color-coded) if the rg is significantly different from the rg with the general F1 factor. To arrive at a p-value for this difference, we used Monte Carlo simulation to resample the correlation matrix, refer to script 6b.

F1 <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_f1.RDS") 
F2 <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_f2.RDS") 
F3 <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_f3.RDS") 
F4 <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_f4.RDS")

labels <- fread("scripts/labels.csv")

res <- rbind(F1, F2, F3, F4)

# Combine and add the labels

res <- res %>% 
  mutate(p_value = ifelse(p_value == "< 5e-300", 5e-300, p_value)) %>% 
  mutate(p_value = as.numeric(p_value)) %>% 
  full_join(labels, by = c("rhs" = "short")) %>% 
  mutate(Category = fct_relevel(Category, "Psychiatric", "Physical", "SES/ cognitive", "Social")) 

# We add the p-values for the difference derived using Monte Carlo simulation

F2pvalues <- fread("results/factor_rg/rg_EFA4_diff_F2_p.tsv")
F3pvalues <- fread("results/factor_rg/rg_EFA4_diff_F3_p.tsv")
F4pvalues <- fread("results/factor_rg/rg_EFA4_diff_F4_p.tsv")

pvalues <- rbind(F2pvalues, F3pvalues, F4pvalues) %>% 
  mutate(lhs = paste0("F", factor)) %>% 
  rename(rhs = trait, diff_rg_p = p) 

res <- res %>% 
  left_join(pvalues) %>% 
  select(lhs, label, STD_Genotype, STD_Genotype_SE, p_value, Category, diff_rg_p) %>% 
  rename(rg = STD_Genotype, SE = STD_Genotype_SE) %>% 
  mutate(lhs = recode(lhs, "F1" = "F1-Smoking/other", "F2" = "F2-Dependence", "F3" = "F3-Alcohol", "F4" = "F4-Cannabis")) %>% 
  mutate(lhs = as_factor(lhs)) 

# Correct for multiple testing

res <- res %>% 
  group_by(lhs) %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr = p.adjust(as.numeric(p_value), "BH")) %>% 
  mutate(diff_rg_p_fdr = p.adjust(diff_rg_p), "BH") %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr_bin = ifelse(p_fdr < 0.05, "sig", "nonsig")) %>% 
  mutate(diff_rg_p_fdr_bin = ifelse(diff_rg_p_fdr < 0.05, "*", " ")) %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr_bin = as_factor(p_fdr_bin)) 

# Order by correlation with G

res <- res %>%
  mutate(rg_F1 = ifelse(lhs == "F1-General/smok", rg, NA)) %>%
  arrange(desc(rg_F1)) %>%
  mutate(label = factor(label, levels = unique(label)))

# Save ordering for the other plots
order <- as_tibble(res$label)

# Plot

plt_efa <- ggplot(res, aes(x = rg, y = fct_rev(label), color = lhs, shape = p_fdr_bin, fill = p_fdr_bin)) + 
  geom_pointrange(aes(xmin = rg - 1.96 * as.numeric(SE), xmax = rg + 1.96 * as.numeric(SE)), 
                  position = position_dodge(width = -0.65),
                  size = 0.3, fatten = 2) +
  facet_grid(Category ~ ., scales = "free", space = "free_y") +
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(-1.1, 1.4)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, size = 0.15) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 1.1, size = 0.05) +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank()) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        strip.text = element_text(colour = 'black', size = 8),
        strip.background = element_rect(fill = "lightgrey", color = "black"),
        panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA), 
        plot.title = element_text(size = 10, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5)
  ) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("grey30", "#D62728", "#984EA3", "#4DAF4A"), name = NULL) +
  scale_shape_manual(values = c(19, 21)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(NA, "white")) +
  xlab("Genetic Correlation") +
  guides(shape = "none", fill = "none") +
  ggtitle("By EFA-factors") +
  geom_text(aes(x = 1.3, y = fct_rev(label), color = lhs, label = diff_rg_p_fdr_bin, group = lhs, size = 2), 
            position = position_dodge(width = -0.65),
            show.legend = FALSE)


plt_efa

ggsave("results/factor_rg/rg_efa.svg", plt_efa, width = 7.2, height = 9)

plt_efa_b <- plt_efa + ggtitle("")
ggsave("results/factor_rg/rg_efa.png", plt_efa_b, width = 7, height = 7, dpi=600) 
ggsave("paper/mainfigures/Figure 5 - EFA gencor.svg", plt_efa_b, width = 7.2, height = 9)
ggsave("paper/mainfigures/Figure 5 - EFA gencor.png", plt_efa_b, width = 7.2, height = 9)
fwrite(res, "results/factor_rg/factor_rg_EFA.csv")

By substance

Next, we compare the correlations for G and specific substance factors.

SMK <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_smk.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G")
ALC <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_alc.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G")
CAN <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_can.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G")
G <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_gbysub.RDS")

res <- rbind(SMK, ALC, CAN, G)

# Combine and add the labels

res <- res %>% 
  mutate(p_value = ifelse(p_value == "< 5e-300", 5e-300, p_value)) %>% 
  mutate(p_value = as.numeric(p_value)) %>% 
  full_join(labels, by = c("rhs" = "short")) %>% 
  mutate(Category = fct_relevel(Category, "Psychiatric", "Physical", "SES/ cognitive", "Social")) 

# To add difference scores, pivot the table to wide format and back

res <- res %>% 
  select(lhs, label, STD_Genotype, STD_Genotype_SE, p_value, Category) %>% 
  rename(rg = STD_Genotype, SE = STD_Genotype_SE) %>% 
  mutate(lhs = fct_relevel(lhs, "SMK", "ALC", "CAN", "G")) %>% 
  mutate(lhs = recode(lhs, "SMK" = "Smoking", "ALC" = "Alcohol", "CAN" = "Cannabis", "G" = "General"))

# Correct for multiple testing

res <- res %>% 
  mutate(p_bin = ifelse((rg < 0 & rg + 1.96 * as.numeric(SE) < 0) | (rg > 0 & rg - 1.96 * as.numeric(SE) > 0) , "*", "")) %>% 
  group_by(lhs) %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr = p.adjust(as.numeric(p_value), "BH")) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr_bin = ifelse(p_fdr < 0.05, "sig", "nonsig")) %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr_bin = as_factor(p_fdr_bin)) 

# Order same as EFA plot

order <- order %>% distinct()
res$label <- factor(res$label, levels = order$value)

# Plot

plt_sub <- ggplot(res, aes(x = rg, y = fct_rev(label), color = lhs, shape = p_fdr_bin, fill = p_fdr_bin)) + 
  geom_pointrange(aes(xmin = rg - 1.96 * as.numeric(SE), xmax = rg + 1.96 * as.numeric(SE)), 
                  position = position_dodge(width = -0.65),
                  size = 0.3, fatten = 2) +
  facet_grid(Category ~ ., scales = "free", space = "free_y") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, size = 0.15) +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank()) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        strip.text = element_text(colour = 'black', size = 8),
        strip.background = element_rect(fill = "lightgrey", color = "black"),
        panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA), 
        plot.title = element_text(size = 10, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5)
  ) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("#377EB8", "#984EA3", "#4DAF4A", "grey30"), name = NULL) +
  scale_shape_manual(values = c(19, 21)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(NA, "white")) +
  xlab("Genetic Correlation") +
  guides(shape = "none", fill = "none") +
  ggtitle("By substance")

By substance - comparing to model without G

SMK <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_smk.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G")
SMK_orig <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_smk_withoutG.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G") %>% 
  mutate(lhs = "SMK_orig")

ALC <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_alc.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G")
ALC_orig <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_alc_withoutG.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G") %>% 
  mutate(lhs = "ALC_orig")

CAN <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_can.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G")
CAN_orig <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_can_withoutG.RDS") %>% 
  filter(lhs != "G") %>% 
  mutate(lhs = "CAN_orig")

G <- readRDS("results/factor_rg/rg_gbysub.RDS")

res <- rbind(SMK, SMK_orig, ALC, ALC_orig, CAN, CAN_orig, G)

# Combine and add the labels

labels <- fread("scripts/labels.csv")

res <- res %>% 
  mutate(p_value = ifelse(p_value == "< 5e-300", 5e-300, p_value)) %>% 
  mutate(p_value = as.numeric(p_value)) %>% 
  full_join(labels, by = c("rhs" = "short")) %>% 
  mutate(Category = fct_relevel(Category, "Psychiatric", "Physical", "SES/ cognitive", "Social")) 

# To add difference scores, pivot the table to wide format and back

res <- res %>% 
  select(lhs, label, STD_Genotype, STD_Genotype_SE, p_value, Category) %>% 
  rename(rg = STD_Genotype, SE = STD_Genotype_SE) %>% 
  mutate(lhs = fct_relevel(lhs, "SMK", "SMK_orig", "ALC", "ALC_orig", "CAN", "CAN_orig", "G")) %>% 
  mutate(lhs = recode(lhs, "SMK" = "Smoking", "SMK_orig" = "Smoking original", "ALC" = "Alcohol", "ALC_orig" = "Alcohol original", "CAN" = "Cannabis", "CAN_orig"= "Cannabis original", "G" = "General"))

# Correct for multiple testing

res <- res %>% 
  mutate(p_bin = ifelse((rg < 0 & rg + 1.96 * as.numeric(SE) < 0) | (rg > 0 & rg - 1.96 * as.numeric(SE) > 0) , "*", "")) %>% 
  group_by(lhs) %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr = p.adjust(as.numeric(p_value), "BH")) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr_bin = ifelse(p_fdr < 0.05, "sig", "nonsig")) %>% 
  mutate(p_fdr_bin = as_factor(p_fdr_bin)) 

# Order by correlation with G

res <- res %>%
  mutate(rg_G = ifelse(lhs == "General", rg, NA)) %>%
  arrange(desc(rg_G)) %>%
  mutate(label = factor(label, levels = unique(label)))

# Plot

plt_sub <- ggplot(res, aes(x = rg, y = fct_rev(label), color = lhs, shape = p_fdr_bin, fill = p_fdr_bin)) + 
  geom_pointrange(aes(xmin = rg - 1.96 * as.numeric(SE), xmax = rg + 1.96 * as.numeric(SE)), 
                  position = position_dodge(width = -0.75),
                  size = 0.3, fatten = 2) +
  facet_grid(Category ~ ., scales = "free", space = "free_y") +
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(-1.1, 1.4)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, size = 0.15) +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank()) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        axis.title.x = element_text(size = 13),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 13),
        strip.text = element_text(colour = 'black', size = 13),
        strip.background = element_rect(fill = "lightgrey", color = "black"),
        panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA), 
        plot.title = element_text(size = 13, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 13)
  ) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("#377EB8", "#B9D8F2", "#984EA3", "#dba1e3", "#4DAF4A", "#8ade87", "grey30"), name = NULL) +
  scale_shape_manual(values = c(19, 21)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(NA, "white")) +
  xlab("Genetic Correlation") +
  guides(shape = "none", fill = "none") +
  ggtitle("By substance")
